  "creatorLens": "Reader understands that the gap between 'a URL exists' and 'an LLM can use its content' is wider than it looks — JavaScript rendering, dynamic loading, cookie walls, CSS selectors. The hosted r.jina.ai/s.jina.ai approach is clever (URL prefix = zero-config), but the repo is a thin web service wrapper, not a reusable library. The pattern is valuable; the implementation is a hosted dependency.",
